Citizen TV special projects editor Asha Mwilu has announced she has left Royal Media Services Ltd to concentrate on her start-up. Asha joined Royal Media in April 2018 and has featured in various projects, including the Mara Heist expose which was aired in 2019. She previously worked with Kenya Television Network (KTN) as a senior reporter for politics and special projects. Asha covered current affairs, security and political stories while at KTN before exiting. She announced her move on Twitter and thanked Citizen TV editors who have walked with her. Fellow journalists took to Twitter to congratulate her.